<item>
            <title>[FLINK-11630] TaskExecutor does not wait for Task termination when terminating itself</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-11630</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;TaskExecutor&lt;/tt&gt; does not properly wait for the termination of &lt;tt&gt;Tasks&lt;/tt&gt; when terminating. In fact, it does not even trigger the cancellation of the running &lt;tt&gt;Tasks&lt;/tt&gt;. I think for better lifecycle management it is important that the &lt;tt&gt;TaskExecutor&lt;/tt&gt; triggers the termination of all running &lt;tt&gt;Tasks&lt;/tt&gt; and then wait until all &lt;tt&gt;Tasks&lt;/tt&gt; have terminated before it terminates itself.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
